Kaneka Corp. (4118) , a Japanese maker of
synthetic resins, said its 12.7 megawatt solar power plant in
central Japan began operations on Oct. 1.  The plant in Ibaraki prefecture uses thin-film silicon
modules produced by Kaneka, the Osaka-based company said today
in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
